news.title: Mumbai: Two prime flats owned by Harshad Mehta's crony up for auction
news.para: The two flats - each measuring 1,150 square feet super built-up - No 202 and 301 in Vandana CHS, Janki Kutir plot, at posh Juhu, are now proposed to be auctioned through public tenders by November 25.

news.title: Adler Group sells 20% of property portfolio to LEG Immobilien
news.para: The sales price for the 15,350 apartments and 185 commercial units will be slightly below the property valuation as Adler will keep a 10.1% stake for tax reasons, it added.

news.title: China's Harbin announce measures to support builders
news.para: Developers should get back part of their presale funds held in government escrow accounts as quickly as possible to relieve pressure on their cashflows, the government of Harbin, the capital of northeastern Heilongjiang province, said on Sunday in a statement on its website.

news.title: Court grants time to Avantha Group's promoter to advance arguments on bail plea
news.para: The ED was probing an alleged transaction between his company Avantha Realty, Yes Bank co-founder Rana Kapoor and his wife, who are already being investigated under the PMLA by the agency.

news.title: China's Fantasia limits bond trading; Modern Land seeks to delay repayment
news.para: Modern Land (China) Co, a smaller developer, said it was seeking consent from investors to extend the maturity date of a dollar bond due on Oct. 25 by three months in order to avoid a default.

news.title: Four years on, only 15 of 60 Trichy smart city projects over
news.para: ​With only 15 proposals completed and launched for public use, the urban local body has 45 more to complete of which work is yet to commence on at least three infrastructure projects.

news.title: Sunteck Realty's sales bookings jump 36% to Rs 272 crore in Q2 FY22
news.para: In a regulatory filing, the Mumbai-based developer informed that collections from customers rose 47 per cent to Rs 207 crore in the second quarter of this fiscal year as against Rs 141 crore in the corresponding period of the previous year.

news.title: Rabindra Sarani building tenants to approach Kolkata civic body for urgent repair
news.para: At least 23 families staying there as tenants were willing to create a common fund for taking up urgent repair work of the sprawling mansion which has over 100 rooms.

news.title: Need better rehabilitation plan in second phase of Noida airport, say villagers
news.para: A public hearing of the social impact assessment report prepared by Gautam Buddha University, which was to be held on Sunday, has been deferred because the administration has sought a few more details.

news.title: Government will assess stability of TNHB buildings: Tamil Nadu housing minister
news.para: The minister said all TNHB buildings identified as weak across the state would be examined and necessary action would be taken based on suggestions given by experts.

news.title: Nagpur: Over 370 building plans sanctioned from April-Aug 2021
news.para: Between April and August in the current fiscal, Nagpur Municipal Corporation (NMC) has sanctioned 374 building plans, which is 2.3 times the numbers registered during the corresponding period last fiscal.

news.title: China Evergrande bondholders brace for coupon deadline due October 11
news.para: Expectations that the company will make the semi-annual payments on its April 2022, April 2023 and April 2024 notes due Oct. 11 are slim as it prioritises onshore creditors and remains silent on its dollar debt obligations.

news.title: Ensure only one registry in a floor in licensed colonies: DTCP to tehsildars
news.para: The order followed a directive from deputy commissioner Yash Garg, who instructed the district town planner to ensure there was no violation of norms.

news.title: Maharashtra: High premiums hit conversion of collector's land to freehold units
news.para: Over 1,250 such plots have been given by the government to individuals and housing societies in south Mumbai, and only 19 plot holders have sought conversion to freehold.

news.title: Tamil Nadu RERA to handle disputes over projects built before 2016
news.para: “If the cause of action survives after coming into force of the RERA Act, TNRERA gets jurisdiction over all the disputes pertaining to the real estate projects,” the order said.
